SIMPLE: unstring
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unstring
<hw>Un*string"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>string</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To deprive of a string or strings; also, to take
from a string; <as>as, to <ex>unstring</ex> beads</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To loosen the string or strings of; <as>as, to
<ex>unstring</ex> a harp or a bow</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To relax the tension of; to loosen.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧His
garland they <xex>unstring</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Dryden.</au>
<def2><def>Used also figuratively; <as>as, his nerves were
<ex>unstrung</ex> by fear</as>.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unstriped</ent>⟦br⟧
